QLALib is a group of classes and functions designed for use in quantum mechanics applications. The library interfaces with the C++ Boost libraries and the GNU Scientific Libraries (GSL). Basic installation is as follows:
In the base directory,

1) glibtoolize
2) aclocal
3) autoheader
4) automake -a
5) autoconf
6) ./configure
7) make
8) make install

To link to QLALib, invoke the -lQLA flag at linking time